I"ˆ3<p>Intermittent fasting, currently one of the worldâ€™s most popular health trends, is an eating plan where you switch between eating and fasting on a regular schedule. Unlike most diets, itâ€™s not concerned with <em>what</em> you eat, but rather <em>when</em> you eat.</p>

<p>There are a number of apps and services that can help keep track of your fasting. One of these apps is Zero.</p>

<h1 id="onboarding">Onboarding</h1>
<p>Zero is available on the <a href="https://apps.apple.com/ke/app/zero-simple-fasting-tracker/id1168348542">App Store</a> and the <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.zerofasting.zero&amp;hl=en_US">Google Play Store</a>. While itâ€™s free to download and use, it also has a subscription plan that enhances the fasting experience.</p>

